@HostAddress = http://localhost:5067

# 1. Login to retrieve the JWT token
# Fill the token in the `@token` variable below to authenticate subsequent requests.
# @name login
POST {{HostAddress}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "bilal.ahmed@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

###

# Copy the value of $.data.token from the login response and paste it below:
@token = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..JguJ2rIh17ZdFeFZ2e9DA7WTHJYXt-OFpWAu7gm3Vk4
###

# 2. Get Users (Paginated, Filterable, Sortable)
# Try changing query parameters: pageNumber, pageSize, orderBy
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/v1/users?pageNumber=1&pageSize=10&orderBy=LastName desc
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# 3. Get User By ID
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/v1/users/1022
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# 4. Create a New User
POST {{HostAddress}}/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "firstName": "Ismail",
  "lastName": "Malik",
  "email": "zia.fyp26+new@hazelsoft.org"
}

###

# 5. Update an Existing User (Note: Email property is no longer editable)
PUT {{HostAddress}}/api/v1/users/1022
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "firstName": "Bilal",
  "lastName": "Ahmed Updated"
}

###

# 6. Delete a User
DELETE {{HostAddress}}/api/v1/users/1025
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# 7. Dynamic Filtering Tests using System.Linq.Dynamic.Core (Success Cases)

# 7.1 Filter by exact email (string equality)
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/v1/users?filters=Email == "bilal.ahmed@example.com"
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# 7.2 Filter by partial matching (case-insensitive contains using string method)
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/v1/users?filters=FirstName.ToLower().Contains("sar")
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# 7.3 Filter by Boolean state
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/v1/users?filters=EmailConfirmed == true
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# 7.4 Filter by numeric comparison (greater than)
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/v1/users?filters=Id > 1023
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# 7.5 Combined Filters: EmailConfirmed AND Numeric ID (using 'and' operator)
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/v1/users?filters=EmailConfirmed == true and Id > 1022
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# 7.6 Combined Filters using OR logic
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/v1/users?filters=FirstName.Contains("Sarah") or FirstName.Contains("Bilal")
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# 7.7 Combined Filters with OrderBy and Pagination
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/v1/users?filters=EmailConfirmed == true and Id > 1022&orderBy=FirstName desc&pageNumber=1&pageSize=5
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# 8. Dynamic Filtering Tests (Validation Failure Cases - Expected 400 Bad Request)

# 8.1 Wrong type format (Boolean parsing error)
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/v1/users?filters=EmailConfirmed == "not_a_boolean"
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# 8.2 Non-existent property name
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/v1/users?filters=Age == 25
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# 8.3 Invalid operator / syntax error
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/v1/users?filters=EmailConfirmed = true
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
